**Not Specific to your fix but FYI on classes**

There are different ways you can use the classes. You can use the attributes of the parent class which in your case is `Displays`. You do not need the parenthesis around it when making a class unless you are passing a parent class through a subclass to inherit its attributes. 

When you have inherited the parent class you can add attributes without changing the parent class. This example uses the `super().__init__` method to add information, it also adds the attribute `page_options`.

