Finally figured it out.
In our Angular 5 code, we had a material-overrides.scss file.  In it, somebody had added the following style:
```
mat-dialog-container {
  opacity: 0;
  @include transform(translate3d(0, 3.5rem, 0));
  @include transition(opacity $animation-time, -webkit-transform $animation-time);
}
```
When I commented out the opacity: 0, my dialogs started to appear.  Not sure why we had this in Angular 5 (material 2.0.0-beta).  Didn&#39;t seem to cause any issues then, but it did now.  Anyway, problem solved.

